The paper discusses a system for patent and article tracking, retrieval, and analysis, which involves the usage of multiple retrieval models and regression models for merging the results. This indicates that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the usage of patent metadata and citation structures, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Digital Libraries (cs.DL) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the creation of initial working sets and final re-ranking regression models, which could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on patent search and analysis could also place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category.
